{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b5335539-38d9-42f4-8d97-d47cf8c38c4b","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` but depends on it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GpCAxauaSGEyzA71LVAKiL","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# compile order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Lk5ZNoLgoq4FQd5NH4nZVr","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c22598e2ac5d4103ba4f6cc397ad6310/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c22598e2ac5d4103ba4f6cc397ad6310/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"a9d9eb38-45b2-410a-8b6f-62a941b5b6fb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed earlier in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":387,"requestId":"441B:3EB10:16E7BC1:19F98FA:69FE84FE"},"id":"4bdf03ae-715b-457b-bfa5-edbb72dc9ef6","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:18.490Z","parentId":"c07ff462-b14c-41c1-a127-bfbbd22f1c82"}
